p: Among participants 9 years and older, 87% of influenza A(H3N2) cases and 94% of controls who reported 2018/19 vaccination also reported 2017/18 vaccination, with lower VE among repeat recipients (−1%; 95% CI: −45 to 29) compared with those who received the vaccine in 2018/19 only (69%; 95% CI: 18 to 89) ( Supplementary Table S10). Of the 30 clade 3C.3a cases that were 9 years and older and vaccinated in 2018/19, all reported also being vaccinated in 2017/18; VE against clade 3C.3a for dually vaccinated relative to dually unvaccinated participants was −115% (95% CI: −304 to −15).
